{"MAVERICK":[{"def":"In the southwestern part of the united States, a bullock or heifer that has not been branded, and is unclaimed or wild; -- said to be from Maverick, the name of a cattle owner in Texas who naglected to brand his cattle.","pos":""}],"MAVERICK BRAND":[{"def":"A brand originated by a dishonest cattleman, who, without owning any stock, gradually accumulates a herd by finding mavericks.","pos":""}],"MAVIS":[{"def":"The European throstle or song thrush (Turdus musicus).","pos":""},{"def":"My darling; -- an Irish term of endearment for a girl or woman.","pos":""}]}